				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Flash! News" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>This is an elaborately accessorized 1937 newspaper game. Players compete to fill a blank front page with articles, matching headlines and pictures. The box is filled with glossy paper slips marked with a category on the back and either a headline or story on the front. The stories are actual news events from the time (including some false versions).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In turn, a player rolls 2D6, which requires drawing the top slip of paper from the appropriate box. These boxes are: 2 - Must (a story that must be included); 3 - Hold for Release (a story that cannot be put on the page until released by another event; 4 - City Editor; 5 - Telegraph Editor; 6 - News Editor (allows drawing a headline or a A-sized short story); 7 - Take a C-Short story; 8 - Take a B-Short story; 9 - Copy Desk (also allows choosing a headline or an A-Short; 10 - Picture Editor; 11 - Scoop; 12 - Flash. The last two are the only ways to get &amp;quot;Special&amp;quot; stories.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players may rearrange their pages at any time, and &amp;quot;Go to Press&amp;quot; as soon as their pages are full. When all but one player has gone to press, the remaining player follows a process to fill in the page immediately.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The articles on each page are then rated against a secret key of circulation values. These values are added up for each player, and the one with the highest total circulation wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
